@l0rd: I did not test the default WSL podman (fedora based) instance, can give it a try. I default to ubuntu and been using podman with ubuntu in WSL2 for the last ~5 years, so a natural choice for me to evaluate composefs support in also.

Regarding the plain alpine image as mentioned in the initiating issue description, I did not try to verify it with it again after getting my testscenario to work (which set up a more easily verifiable scenario in terms of deduplication at file level). Will try to repeat with a clean slate, and pull the plain alpine:latest and check if the folder structure shows the expected output, like the one I got to work with my testimages

Update: tested with alpine:latest again, with the expected results, unfortunately not able remember exactly the circumstances when I tried with alpine:latest, triggering filing the issue/question, maybe when I failed to get any expected output from local builds, then trying with an external image, pulling alpine latest and second latest, naively checking storage and not noticing any obvious savings

@giuseppe : Ok, maybe not a very useful use case, but one I ran into when testing, not a production scenario issue thou.
